[normal] The Merton Rule was the first local planning policy to set a requirement for renewable energy generation in new buildings, developed by Merton Borough Council in 2003. The rule required any new residential development of more than 10 units, or any commercial building over 1,000m
[normal]2
[normal], to generate at least 10% of its energy needs from on-site renewable energy equipment: 
[normal]www.merton.gov.uk/environment/planning/planningpolicy/mertonrule.htm
